    "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nLSP diagnostics get stuck / stop working after running `:e!` command on neovim. See screenrecording:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/assets/36432023/071f5ebb-f00a-4b8d-9dc3-47ecd9c10937\r\n\r\n### Neovim version\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.4\r\nBuild type: Release\r\nLuaJIT 2.1.1692716794\r\n\r\n### Nvim-lspconfig version\r\n\r\n7fedba8b1f8d0080c775851c429b88fd2ed4c6f5\r\n\r\n### Operating system and version\r\n\r\nDebian GNU/Linux VERSION=\"10 (buster)\"\r\n\r\n### Affected language servers\r\n\r\ntsserver\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Setup a language server\r\n2. Make a file change that triggers a diagnostic\r\n3. Write `:e!` on neovim command mode and press Enter\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n4. Now the diagnostic is stuck, it won't work for that particular file until you restart `:LspRestart`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nDiagnostics shouldn't be stuck, they should be able to keep working after `:e!`\r\n\r\n### Minimal config\r\ninit.vim\r\n```\r\ncall plug#begin('~/.vim-plugged')\r\nPlug 'neovim/nvim-lspconfig'\r\ncall plug#end()\r\n\r\nlua <<EOF\r\n  local lspconfig = require('lspconfig')\r\n  require('lspconfig')['tsserver'].setup {}\r\nEOF\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### LSP log\r\n\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/andrescuco/930182635d7acdbbb174eae6a2e5a1e4",
